# Frontend component layout

**Reusable UI** (anything you would import and compose) must follow this layout **wherever it lives under `src/`**—not only under `src/components/`. Parent directories (`src/lib/…`, `src/features/…`, etc.) only group features; the component folder pattern is the same.

**Out of scope** (keep as framework expects): root shells such as `App.svelte`, `main.ts` entry wiring, and SvelteKit route files like `+page.svelte` / `+layout.svelte` unless you are deliberately colocating a dedicated widget next to a route using this pattern.

## Structure

For a component whose folder name is `<name>` (kebab-case, e.g. `action-button`):

```text
src/<...>/<name>/
  index.ts              # Re-export the component (and types if any)
  <name>.svelte         # The Svelte component
  <name>.stories.ts     # Story definitions
  <name>.test.ts        # Unit / component tests
```

- **Folder name** = public component id; **`index.ts`**, **`<name>.svelte`**, **`<name>.stories.ts`**, **`<name>.test.ts`** all share that basename.
- **`index.ts`** is the stable import surface for consumers outside the folder.

When adding or refactoring reusable UI, create or move files to match this layout. If stories or tests are not wired yet, still add the placeholder files when introducing a new component so tooling can be adopted without renaming.

